  },
  "primaryContentSections" : [
    {
      "content" : [
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "This part of the book describes the formal grammar of the Swift programming language.",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "The grammar described here is intended to help you understand the language in more",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "detail, rather than to allow you to directly implement a parser or compiler.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The Swift language is relatively small, because many common types, functions, and operators",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "that appear virtually everywhere in Swift code",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "are actually defined in the Swift standard library. Although these types, functions,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "and operators aren’t part of the Swift language itself,",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "they’re used extensively in the discussions and code examples in this part of the book.",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "anchor" : "How-to-Read-the-Grammar",
          "level" : 2,
          "text" : "How to Read the Grammar",
          "type" : "heading"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "The notation used to describe the formal grammar of the Swift programming language",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : " ",
              "type" : "text"
            },
            {
              "text" : "follows a few conventions:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
        {
          "items" : [
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "An arrow (→) is used to mark grammar productions and can be read as “can consist of.”",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Syntactic categories are indicated by ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "italic",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "emphasis"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " text and appear on both sides",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "of a grammar production rule.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Literal words and punctuation are indicated by ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "code" : "boldface constant width",
                          "type" : "codeVoice"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "strong"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " text",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "and appear only on the right-hand side of a grammar production rule.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Alternative grammar productions are separated by vertical",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "bars (|). When alternative productions are too long to read easily,",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "they’re broken into multiple grammar production rules on new lines.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "In a few cases, regular font text is used to describe the right-hand side",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "of a grammar production rule.",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "content" : [
                {
                  "inlineContent" : [
                    {
                      "text" : "Optional syntactic categories and literals are marked by a trailing",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : " ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : "question mark, ",
                      "type" : "text"
                    },
                    {
                      "inlineContent" : [
                        {
                          "text" : "?",
                          "type" : "text"
                        }
                      ],
                      "type" : "emphasis"
                    },
                    {
                      "text" : ".",
                      "type" : "text"
                    }
                  ],
                  "type" : "paragraph"
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "type" : "unorderedList"
        },
        {
          "inlineContent" : [
            {
              "text" : "As an example, the grammar of a getter-setter block is defined as follows:",
              "type" : "text"
            }
          ],
          "type" : "paragraph"
        },
